<div class="quotetitle">Snaer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Well actually I mostly use FCEultra but I use nesticle sometimes <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarassed" /> (very rarely though).<br /></div><br />Well, if you like to use it for playing, that's your call, but please never use it for development purposes (like comparing your emulator to it).<br /><br />FCEU isn't terribly accurate either. It's great because it originated debugging versions that are insanely useful, but it doesn't do a great job out of simulating several obscure details of the console.<br /><br />The consensus is that Nestopia and Nintendulator are the most accurate emulators, so you should always use those for development purposes. But having an actual console to run tests on is a good idea too. I have programmed stuff that these two emulators were fine with, but they looked wrong on the actual console.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Feb 04, 2010 3:58 am</p><hr />
